Video`VideoPart:
ObjectType: Symbol
Usage: Video`VideoPart[vid: _Video|_VideoStream|_?VideoHandleQ, spec]
extracts a list of images from vid.

spec can be:
	a number (interpreted as time in seconds)
	a time quantity
	a "Frames" quantity
	a Interval specification containing any of the above

The options are:
	"CallingFunction" -> Video`VideoPart
	"Step" -> Automatic
	MaxItems -> Infinity
	VideoTracks -> 1

"Step" will be used if spec is All or an Interval an its values can be:
	a number (interpreted as time in seconds)
	a time quantity
	a "Frames" quantity
	Into[n] returns uniformly spaced frames in ROI
	{"Random", Into[n]} returns random uniformly distributed frames in ROI
The value of VideoTracks can be an integer, a list of integers or All.
Messages will be issued with the head specified in the "CallingFunction" option
